org.flossware.jcore.collections.collection

Interface FunctionalCollection<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of value found in a collection.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<V>, Iterable<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFunctionalCollection, DefaultFunctionalCollection

    public interface FunctionalCollection<V>
extends Collection<V>
    Represents a "functional" set which allows us to extend the core functions with values that return self so we can chain calls. Similar to what one can do with StringBuilder. For example: functionalCollection.add("X").add("Y")
    Author:
    sfloess
